entries.title: China Refused U.S. Call After Downing of Suspected Spy Balloon, Pentagon Says
entries.description: Washington and Beijing already face a relationship strained by trade and Taiwan tensions.

entries.title: Poland Weighs More U.S. Weapons Ahead of Biden Visit
entries.description: Moves come as the administration seeks to shore up support for Ukraine at home and abroad.

entries.title: Syria Reels From Earthquakes but Struggles to Tap Outside Aid
entries.description: The country faces hurdles because of border closures, the political isolation of President Bashar al-Assad and his government’s policy of starving rebels of assistance.

entries.title: Tricky Faults, Lax Construction and Wobbly Soil Fueled Destruction in Turkey
entries.description: The first earthquake loaded stress onto another fault in the region, according to a seismologist.

entries.title: David Carrick, Former London Police Officer, Gets 30 Years in Prison for Rape
entries.description: The case has led to calls for the Met police force to revamp its vetting process and root out other suspected sexual abusers.

entries.title: Can Developing Economies Have High Growth Without Using Coal? A Debate.
entries.description: Two experts square off on a question that will confront emerging nations in the coming years.

entries.title: China Has More ICBM Launchers Than U.S., American Military Says
entries.description: The U.S. military has notified Congress that China now has more land-based intercontinental-range missile launchers than the U.S., fueling the debate about how Washington should respond to Beijing’s nuclear buildup.

entries.title: Lawmakers' Support for Macron's Pension Overhaul in France Falters
entries.description: Proposal to raise retirement age has struck a nerve and sparked protest—leading some lawmakers from the president’s own party to threaten to vote against the measure.

entries.title: Border-Town Warehouses Are Booming as More Manufacturing Moves to Mexico
entries.description: Real-estate investors are adding properties in cities such as Tijuana, Mexico, and Laredo and El Paso, Texas.

entries.title: Russia Pushes on Several Fronts in Ukraine
entries.description: Russian forces launched multiple attacks in eastern Ukraine, pushing for a breakthrough on the battlefield ahead of the delivery of new Western weapons.

entries.title: Thailand Pins Hopes on Return of Chinese Tourists
entries.description: Vacationers from China, absent for years because of Beijing’s strict zero-Covid policy, are vital to the revival of the country’s travel industry.

entries.title: Earthquake Rescue Efforts in Turkey, Syria Hampered by Snow
entries.description: Snow, freezing temperatures and blocked roads hindered efforts to rescue survivors trapped under collapsed buildings across southern Turkey and northern Syria after two powerful earthquakes killed more than 5,000 people.

entries.title: Reserve Bank of Australia Raises Rates, Signals More to Come
entries.description: The RBA’s stance suggests global central banks are headed down different paths as their battle with inflation enters a new phase.
